diagnosis.final_diagnosis: Infiltrating ductal carcinoma of the breast, HER2-positive, with metastases to the liver.
diagnosis.diagnostic_reasoning: The final diagnosis of HER2-positive breast cancer was supported by imaging studies revealing spiculated masses in the right breast, pathological examination showing invasive ductal carcinoma with HER2 overexpression, and confirmed liver metastases through imaging findings of multiple hepatic lesions.
